<Content>Average October 04. Just spent 4 nights at this hotel. Hotel was ok and made a good base. It is reasonably central, so not far to reach the tourist spots, though not keen at night as it is in a quiet area with not much around for evening entertainment ie restaurants, bars etc. The room was small but was very clean and anything used was replenished, also my favourite... clean sheets every day. The reason I give it 3* is the food, we tried room service breakfast which was expensive but I don't mind if it's edible... this wasn't. Also one evening we were tired so we decided to eat in the hotel restaurant...big mistake, though it looks nice, we were the only people in there, which seemed odd, but then the food we had was very expensive for what it was and disappointing. The hotel bar was ok and I found the staff on reception helpful though one gave us the wrong information one evening so it was a costly cab ride that turned out to be a waste of time. Even though I have been a bit negative we my review we did enjoy our stay in Barcelona. 
