<Author>johnhp
<Content>Beg to differ with the positive reviews I read the reviews before our trip to Barcelona and was quite looking forward to it.However, on arrival It was back to reality. Having been allocated a tiny room on the 5th (top) floor, we went down to reception to ask for a nicer room - were told in a condecending tone We are full, and have no more rooms. You will have to stay in this one. The bathroom was a similar size to the room, which had a 2 feet border around the bed, and not much more. Also, the marble corridor outside echoed everyones' footsteps, and the door and walls didn't keep out much noise .... We also had the benefit of partaking in the party in the room next door, from our room, where we could hear everything ! The police were finally called at 4am, and we got to sleep around 5am - not the best preparation for a meeting at 0930 ...When approached that morning about the incident, staff shrugged, and also advised us that there was a wedding in the hotel the following night, so that even if they could move us, it would be more noisy on other lower floors. So tough luck, in other words! Staff attitude was generally VERY poor in every encounter, whether just meeting them in the corridor, or at reception.Our room neighbours were actually quiet the following night, whether they were moved or had checked out, but there was still quite a lot of noise from the corridor, from people exiting the roof bar, etc.In any case, couldn't recommend the hotel for any reason other than it was close to our meeting location. We would have moved hotel, but the city was quite fully booked, and rates were very high for other locations. On our next trip we will stay at the Hilton and take a taxi ! 
