<Content>Loved it My boyfriend and I stayed here last week for 3 night and it was great. The hotel is very modern and our room was very cool, it was like 3 different rooms, bedroom, study, and bathroom - it was on 2 levels. It's about 5-6 blocks from Plaza Catalyuna which is the center of town, so it's easily accessible to everything but not super easy to run back to get something mid day. Barcelona is such a huge city though that I don't know where would have been any more convienent (and safer) location. The staff was great. One warning however, if you are going to take the train to the airport, I would recommend going to the station at Catalyuna. There is one closer but it was difficult finding the right entrance and there is no ticket office there to ask someone for help. 
