<Content>Worth every euro! The hotel isn't stunning in looks, but it's located near d'Arc the Triomf and central in Barcelona. The room we had was big enough for us. The sleeping erea wasn't to bad and the bathroom is big and clean. And the entire hotel was very clean. The staff speaks English and were there when we needed them. We didn't have diner in the restaurant but you don't want to miss breakfest in this hotel. It's just THE BEST! Fresh fruit and juices....fresh bread in every shape, form and taste. Scrambled eggs, bacon ( all made for you ) ....lot's of sweets ( cakes, cooky's donuts, pie )....my wife liked the fresh pineapple and strawberry's. It's just the perfect way of beginning your day of exploring the city. It's not a tourist hotel, but more for business and therefore not that crowded. We've enjoyed it very much! 
